---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy — keepitmovin"
  description="How the keepitmovin CLI and website handle data."
>
  <article class="docs-content prose standalone-prose container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Trust</p>
    <h1>Privacy</h1>
    <p>
      The keepitmovin CLI does not upload your handoff files, session summaries,
      repository state, or terminal transcript. Those artifacts stay under
      <code>.keepitmovin/</code> in the project where you run it.
    </p>
    <h2>Your coding tools</h2>
    <p>
      Claude Code, Codex, and the other tools launched by keepitmovin still
      communicate with their own providers. Their privacy terms and account
      settings continue to apply.
    </p>
    <h2>This website</h2>
    <p>
      Vercel Analytics records anonymous pageviews and referrers without cookies.
      The Pro early-access form is provided by Tally; information you submit there
      is used only for keepitmovin product research and launch updates.
    </p>
    <h2>Deletion and questions</h2>
    <p>
      Run <code>kim clear</code> to remove local keepitmovin artifacts. To remove a
      waitlist response or ask a privacy question, email
      <a href="mailto:garrett@garrettsiegel.com">garrett@garrettsiegel.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
